      "description": "Fully massless one-loop pentagon in $D = 6 - 2\\varepsilon$ dimensions, five cyclic Mandelstam invariants $s_i = (q_i - q_{i+2})^2$. The paper gives closed-form results for all cuts required by the diagrammatic coaction: the order-$\\varepsilon^1$ maximal cut is $\\ln(-16 \\, \\mathrm{Gram}_5 / (s_1 s_2 s_3 s_4 s_5))$; the order-$\\varepsilon^0$ quadruple cut (all propagators but $i$ on shell) is $\\ln(\\bar{v}/v)$ where $v$ and $\\bar{v}$ are square roots of $16 \\, \\mathrm{Gram}_5$ shifted by the cyclic polynomial in the $s_i$; all triple cuts vanish. Substituting these into the generic pentagon DE reproduces the known Kozlov-Lee differential equation and the symbol letters match a subset of those appearing in two-loop five-point massless integrals.",
